<div dir="ltr">I know Open MPI dropped support for the SPARC V8 ABI some time ago.<div>So, I configured with CC=&quot;gcc -mv8plus&quot;, but I still get:<div><br></div><div><div>checking if have Sparc v8+/v9 support... no</div>
<div>configure: WARNING: Sparc v8 target is not supported in this release of Open MPI.</div><div>configure: WARNING: You must specify the target architecture v8plus</div><div>configure: WARNING: (cc: -xarch=v8plus, gcc: -mcpu=v9) for CFLAGS, CXXFLAGS,</div>
<div>configure: WARNING: FFLAGS, and FCFLAGS to compile Open MPI in 32 bit mode on</div><div>configure: WARNING: Sparc processors</div><div>configure: error: Can not continue.</div><div><br></div><div>So, I am wondering if there is something flawed in the &quot;have Sparc v8+/v9 support&quot; or if gcc&#39;s &quot;-mv8plus&quot; is flawed.</div>
<div>Of course, I will follow the advise in the warning and use -mcpu=v9 instead of -mv8plus, but don&#39;t see why the later didn&#39;t work.  Any ideas what is going on?</div><div><br></div><div>And since this was found in 1.7.4rc2:</div>
